<section class="bright-section bright-section--basf-summary" aria-labelledby="basf-title">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="basf-title">Our Beliefs</h2>
    <p class="bright-muted">
      Christadelphian communities hold to a common summary of Bible teaching. This statement of faith sets out the doctrines we believe Scripture teaches. Below, are the foundation points that summarize the wording our Ecclesias use.
    </p>

    <div class="basf-summary-panel">
      <ul class="basf-cards">
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">1</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">The Bible</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That the Bible is the inspired Word of God, containing the only true record of God&rsquo;s revelation to mankind and being the sole and final authority in all matters of faith and practice.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">2</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">God the Father</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That there is one God, the Father, dwelling in heaven, who is the creator and sustainer of all things. He is immortal, of supreme intelligence, infinite in wisdom, and perfect in moral character.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">3</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Jesus Christ</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That Jesus is the Son of God, born of the virgin Mary, tempted in all points as we are, yet without sin. He died for our sins, was raised from the dead by God, and now sits at the right hand of God as our High Priest and Mediator.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">4</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">The Holy Spirit</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That the Holy Spirit is the power of God, manifested in creation, in the inspiration of the prophets and apostles, in the conception and empowering of Jesus Christ.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">5</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Human nature</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That man is mortal, subject to death as a consequence of sin. We do not possess an immortal soul, but instead await the resurrection that will take place at Christ&rsquo;s return.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">6</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Sin and salvation</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That sin brings death, but through Christ&rsquo;s sacrifice we can receive forgiveness. Salvation comes through faith in Jesus Christ, repentance from sin, and baptism by full immersion in water.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">7</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">The return of Christ</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That Jesus Christ will personally return to the earth to establish the Kingdom of God, to raise and judge the dead, and to reward the faithful with eternal life in that Kingdom.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">8</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">The kingdom of God</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That God will establish His Kingdom on earth with Jerusalem as its capital. Christ will reign as King, bringing peace, righteousness, and prosperity to all nations.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge" aria-hidden="true">9</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Israel</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That the promises made to Abraham and David will be literally fulfilled. Israel will be regathered to their land, and through them God&rsquo;s purpose with the earth will be accomplished.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="basf-card">
          <span class="basf-card__badge basf-card__badge--wide" aria-hidden="true">10</span>
          <h3 class="basf-card__title">Resurrection and judgment</h3>
          <p class="basf-card__text">
            That at Christ&rsquo;s return, the dead will be raised and both living and dead believers will be judged. The righteous will receive eternal life, while the wicked will be destroyed.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bright-section bright-section--distinct" aria-labelledby="distinct-title">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="distinct-title">Some distinctive emphases</h2>
    <p class="bright-muted">
      We share much with other believers who love Scripture. A few areas where Christadelphian teaching is often distinctive include:
    </p>
    <ul class="distinct-grid">
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>One God, the Father</h3>
        <p>We believe in the one God of the Bible; Jesus is the Son of God. The Holy Spirit is God&rsquo;s power, not a separate co-equal person in a trinity.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Mortality and resurrection</h3>
        <p>We are mortal; eternal life is God&rsquo;s gift through resurrection, not an immortal soul leaving the body at death.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>The devil in Scripture</h3>
        <p>We read &ldquo;devil&rdquo; and related language in context&mdash;often referring to sin and opposition to God rather than a personal supernatural evil being.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Kingdom on earth</h3>
        <p>God&rsquo;s kingdom is the restored rule of Christ on earth, centered in the promises to Israel, not a disembodied heaven-only hope.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Conditional immortality</h3>
        <p>Life everlasting is for those in Christ; those who finally reject God are destroyed, not tortured forever.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="distinct-card">
        <h3>Baptism</h3>
        <p>We baptize believers by full immersion as a response to the gospel, following New Testament practice.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

